@startuml yuwen123441_NVMeAutomation

skinparam component {
  BackgroundColor<<Python>> #ADD1B2
  BackgroundColor<<C>> #FFBD9D
  BackgroundColor<<System>> #C0C0C0
}

package "NVMe SSD Automation Test Framework" {
  [Test Cases] <<Python>> as TestCases
  [Test Suites] <<Python>> as TestSuites
  [Common Library] <<Python>> as CommonLib
  [Logic Layer] <<Python>> as LogicLayer
  [Driver (nvme.py)] <<Python>> as Driver
  [Data Structures] <<Python>> as DataStructures
  [Buffer Management] <<Python>> as BufferMgmt
  [NVMe ioctrl Library] <<C>> as IoctlLib
}

[Linux Kernel] <<System>> as Kernel
[NVMe SSD] <<System>> as SSD

TestCases --> TestSuites
TestSuites --> CommonLib
CommonLib --> LogicLayer
LogicLayer --> Driver
Driver --> DataStructures
Driver --> BufferMgmt
Driver --> IoctlLib
IoctlLib --> Kernel
Kernel --> SSD

note right of TestCases
  Implements and executes
  SSD functionality verification
end note

note right of CommonLib
  High-level Python interfaces
  for Admin, I/O, and buffer management
end note

note right of LogicLayer
  Higher-level abstraction for
  NVMe device interaction
end note

note right of Driver
  Python wrapper around
  C library for ioctl calls
end note

note right of IoctlLib
  C library for low-level
  NVMe device interaction
end note

note right of DataStructures
  Python data structures
  for NVMe commands, queues,
  and log pages
end note

note right of BufferMgmt
  Manages memory for
  device driver interaction
end note

@enduml